      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WEBLEC SNIP (4) is worth forgiving last start after finishing fifth (23.82) from Box 7 at Mt Gambier over 400m. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Can discover winning form. LIFE'S A JOURNEY (8) has won here at this journey. The form out of his last race has been franked. Deserves plenty of respect. SEBON DISCO (5) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at her last six runs. Last time finished 2nd on March 29 over 400m at this track behind Toby Keeping beaten 5.5 lengths (22.85) in a Grade 6. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Expected to be in the finish again. MINIATURE FURY (2) did a good job to finish second last time out over 300m at Murray Bridge Straight (17.11) in a Grade 6, the second top-three finish on the trot. Speedy beginner who should be in the action early from an inside box.",
